APPLICATION FOR STAY UNDER SECTION 36(3) OF THE ARBITRATION ACT
Applicant: NHAI (Respondent)

Grounds for stay of the ₹41.65 Cr Arbitral Award:
1. The Tribunal ignored the strict notice requirements under FIDIC Clause 20.1. Emails without formal letters do not constitute valid notice.
2. Patent illegality in awarding Loss of Profit, conflicting with Supreme Court judgments.

Prayer:
NHAI seeks unconditional stay of the Award. 
In the alternative, NHAI proposes to provide a Bank Guarantee rather than depositing the cash amount per the 2019 Amendment to the Act.
